<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880630-0021 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Walgreen Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WAG MHS </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Walgreen Co., Deerfield, Ill., said it definitively agreed to sell its freestanding Wag's family restaurants in Florida and Illinois to Marriott Corp. Terms weren't disclosed.    The operator of drugstores and restaurants said that Marriott, Washington, D.C., has agreed to buy 91 Wag's restaurants, four of which are under construction.    Walgreen has said it planned to shed the restaurants to concentrate on its drugstores, which account for more than 97% of its sales. The company said it will continue to operate 27 restaurants, including some Wag's in shopping malls, Walgreen drugstore cafeterias and Robin Hood family restaurants.    A spokeswoman said the company's goal is to get out of the restaurant business. </TEXT></DOC>